                <head>No. 636<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During his visit to the United States, Chancellor <persName corresp="#p_AK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName> discussed the Saar with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EGADD1">Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> on three occasions. For records of these
                    conversations, see GPT MIN–1 and 2, <ref target="frus1952-54v07p1#d178"
                        >Documents 178</ref> and <ref target="frus1952-54v07p1#d179">179</ref>, and
                    the memorandum of conversation by <persName corresp="#p_MBH1">Morris</persName>,
                    April 14, <ref target="frus1952-54v07p1#d181">Document 181</ref>.</p>
            </div>
